{
  "texts": [
    "We focus on the task of long-form writing, both fictional and non-fictional, under multiple constraints.",
    "When using an LLM for a complex writing task, users might have many constraints in mind and expect lengthy, detailed responses in the form of books, blog posts, etc.",
    "This task is particularly challenging for current LLMs, which struggle with generating coherent long-form outputs (Guan et al., 2021; Wang et al., 2023a), and this difficulty can be amplified when multiple constraints are involved.",
    "Recent instruction-following datasets have featured multi-constraint instructions (Xu et al., 2024; Malaviya et al., 2024) and long-form responses (Köksal et al., 2023; Chen et al., 2024b), but none has integrated these two elements (Table 1).",
    "We bridge this gap by creating Suri, which features complex instructions with multiple constraints and lengthy gold responses (2-5K words, about 3-6K tokens)."
  ]
}